	directory with the setgid bit set.
	[57cb4ad634a3] <1.7>

2012-04-24  Todd C. Miller  <Todd.Miller@courtesan.com>

	* pp:
	Sync with upstream for Mac OS X (and other) fixes.
	[289652f37a92] <1.7>

2012-04-23  Todd C. Miller  <Todd.Miller@courtesan.com>

	* mkpkg:
	Debian sudo has not been built with --with-exempt=sudo since 1.6.8.
	[a2a6efb76e62] <1.7>

	* mkpkg:
	Only build Mac intel universal binary on an intel machine. When
	building on Mac OS X, set SDK_FLAGS if specified osversion doesn't
	match host.
	[ba2542153d30] <1.7>

	* exec_pty.c:
	Add missing initialization of a sigaction structure when I/O
	logging. Fixes a potential problem when suspending the command.
	[6db633c5c9a4] <1.7>

2012-04-08  Todd C. Miller  <Todd.Miller@courtesan.com>

	* config.h.in, configure, configure.in, match.c:
	Do not use GLOB_BRACE or GLOB_TILDE flags to glob()--we want the
	glob() and fnmatch() results to be consistent.
	[dfe105e6150f] <1.7>

2012-03-30  Todd C. Miller  <Todd.Miller@courtesan.com>

	* ldap.c:
	fix typo in last commit
	[30f5d6028ec6] <1.7>

	* alias.c, defaults.c, env.c, exec.c, exec_pty.c, ldap.c, pwutil.c,
	sudo.c, sudoreplay.c, visudo.c:
	Use ecalloc() when allocating structs.
	[79bc1ab2257a] <1.7>

	* alloc.c, alloc.h:
	Add ecalloc().
	[46e4fd731efb] <1.7>

	* bsm_audit.c:
	Use error() instead of log_fatal()
	[95515e1c18da] <1.7>

	* missing.h:
	g/c __unused which is no longer used
	[aa8f78c1a2fc] <1.7>

	* auth/bsdauth.c, auth/kerb5.c, auth/pam.c, auth/sia.c,
	auth/sudo_auth.c, bsm_audit.c, check.c, env.c, iolog.c, logging.c,
	logging.h, parse.c, set_perms.c, sudo.c, sudo_nss.c:
	Remove the NO_EXIT flag to log_error() and add a log_fatal()
	function that exits and is marked no_return. Fixes false positives
	from static analyzers and is easier for humans to read too.
	[781e7c10414d] <1.7>

	* fnmatch.c:
	cast ctype(3) function/macro arguments from char to unsigned char to
	avoid potential negative subscripting.
	[912237612328] <1.7>

	* env.c, sudo.c, sudo.pod:
	When initializing the environment for env_reset, start out with the
	contents of /etc/environment on AIX and login.conf on BSD. Also
	apply environment in login.conf for "sudo -i".
	[71b1a2868b7e] <1.7>

	* TROUBLESHOOTING:
	Add entry for AIX enhanced RBAC config.
	[154944068cf9] <1.7>

	* TROUBLESHOOTING, sudo.c:
	If we are not running with an effective uid of 0, try to give the
	user enough information to debug the problem.
	[613114713cca] <1.7>

	* sudo.c:
	If the "timestampowner" user cannot be resolved, use uid 0 instead
	of exiting with a fatal error.
	[9a17eae432be] <1.7>

	* auth/pam.c, env.c, sudo.h:
	For PAM authentication, merge the PAM environment with the user
	environment in pam_begin_session().
	[078bee18fec1] <1.7>

	* toke.c, toke.l:
	Quiet compiler warning when SELinux is enabled.
	[1c8053173b6e] <1.7>

	* sudo.c:
	Don't read /etc/environment on Linux when using PAM, PAM should set
	the environment variables as needed via pam_env.
	[3319c6cce1e7] <1.7>

	* config.h.in, configure, configure.in:
	Add check for pam_getenvlist()
	[15abe30f755d] <1.7>

	* set_perms.c:
	Use normal error path if unable to set sudoers gid.
	[4ea379c064e9] <1.7>

	* sudo.pp:
	Make sudoersdir relative to PKG_INSTALL_ROOT for Solaris. Make sure
	sudoers file is writable before trying to edit it.
	[38d2be50ba4e] <1.7>

	* config.h.in, configure, configure.in, sudo_noexec.c:
	Add execvpe(), exect(), posix_spawn() and posix_spawnp() wrappers to
	sudo_noexec.c.
	[47745c46665d] <1.7>

2012-03-29  Todd C. Miller  <Todd.Miller@courtesan.com>

	* zlib/adler32.c, zlib/crc32.c, zlib/crc32.h, zlib/deflate.c,
	zlib/deflate.h, zlib/gzguts.h, zlib/gzlib.c, zlib/gzread.c,
	zlib/gzwrite.c, zlib/infback.c, zlib/inffixed.h, zlib/inflate.c,
